Install archlinux


... in device (PC) using external device (USB stick).

Requirements:
- POSIX-oriented operating system https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/POSIX#POSIX-oriented_operating_systems
- curl https://curl.se/download.html

Preparation:
1. plug USB stick to host
2. ISO="$(curl -fs "https://mirror.pkgbuild.com/iso/latest/" | grep -Eo 'archlinux-[0-9]{4}\.[0-9]{2}\.[0-9]{2}-x86_64.iso' | head -n 1)" && curl -o "/tmp/${ISO}" "https://mirror.pkgbuild.com/iso/latest/${ISO}"
3. dd bs=4M if="/tmp/${ISO}" of=/dev/sdx status=progress oflag=sync
4. boot target from USB stick
5. curl -L github.com/pbizopoulos/install-archlinux/raw/master/in-device.sh | bash -s /dev/sda && reboot
6. execute commands in post.txt


... in external device (USB stick) using device (PC).

Requirements:
- archlinux https://archlinux.org/

Preparation:
1. plug USB stick to host
2. sudo pacman -S arch-install-scripts dosfstools reflector
3. curl -L github.com/pbizopoulos/install-archlinux/raw/master/in-device.sh | sudo bash -s /dev/sdb
4. boot target from USB stick
5. execute commands in post.txt


... in qemu using device (PC).

Requirements:
- POSIX-oriented operating system https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/POSIX#POSIX-oriented_operating_systems
- Make https://www.gnu.org/software/make/
- Docker https://docs.docker.com/get-docker/
- Xhost https://www.x.org/releases/X11R7.6/doc/man/man1/xhost.1.xhtml

Preparation:
1. git clone https://github.com/pbizopoulos/install-archlinux
2. cd install-archlinux/
3. sudo systemctl start docker

Usage:
make		# Build image.
make gui	# Run image in QEMU.
make clean 	# Remove tmp/ directory.
